      "lineNbr": 9,
      "author": {
        "id": 1150179
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-21T07:33:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Are preconditions entities?\n\nHow about distinguishing top level entities and something like subtests and preconditions?\nI thought about calling the former entities, and the fomer and the latter collectively subentities.\nEntities are fixtures and top level tests, which are reigsterd to the framework.\nEntities have 1:1 correspondance with *Root.\nSubentities are something that have 1:1 correspondance with *State. e.g. subtests, preconditions, and top level entities.\nI\u0027m not sure if subentities are the best term, but I think it\u0027s something worth discussing.\nWDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 9,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "e3cff6d23556e25989375efbd2c16707f354d454",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e0da113e_8a7bf751",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/internal/testing/state.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 9,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-21T12:38:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s a very good suggestion! Yes, I agree it\u0027s wrong to treat a precondition as an entity.\n\nLet me introduce a term \"semi-entity\" to collectively mention preconditions and hooks. I considered \"subentities\", but \"sub-entity\" sounds like a part of an entity that is still an entity, but preconditions are not entities. (c.f. a subring is a ring, but a semi-ring is NOT a ring.)\n\nI would characterize semi-entities as entry points without metadata. Let me add another paragraph to explain semi-entities.\n\nRegarding subtests, I think subtests are not even semi-entities since they\u0027re not registered to the framework. So we can\u0027t assume 1:1 relationship between State objects and (semi-)entities...",
      "parentUuid": "ae8134d4_f1331f1e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 9,
        "endChar": 40
      },
